    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Particle jets with large transverse momenta, p T , are abundantly produced in highly energetic proton-proton collisions at the CERN LHC, when two partons interact with high momentum transfer under the strong interaction. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The process is described by Quantum Chromodynamics (QCD) using perturbative techniques (pQCD). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The two-final state partons, at leading order (LO) in pQCD, are produced back-to-back in the transverse plane and thus the azimuthal angular separation between the two highest p T jets in the transverse plane, \u2206\u03c6 1,2 = |\u03c6 jet1 \u2212\u03c6 jet2 |, equals \u03c0. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The production of a third or more high-p T jets leads to a deviation from \u03c0 in the azimuthal angle. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The measurement of the azimuthal angular correlation (or decorrelation from \u03c0) in inclusive 2-jet topologies is proven to be an interesting tool to gain insight into multijet production processes. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Previous measurements of azimuthal correlation in inclusive 2-jet topologies were reported by the D0 Collaboration [1,2], ATLAS Collaboration [3], and CMS Collaboration [4,5]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 115,
                    "end": 118,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 118,
                    "end": 120,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "2]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 142,
                    "end": 145,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 169,
                    "end": 172,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "[4,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 172,
                    "end": 174,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "5]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 122,
                    "end": 142,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "ATLAS Collaboration",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Multijet correlations have been measured by the ATLAS collaboration at \u221a s = 7 TeV and \u221a s = 8 TeV [6,7]. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 99,
                    "end": 102,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 102,
                    "end": 104,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "7]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "This paper reports measurements of the normalized inclusive 2-jet cross sections as a function of the azimuthal angular separation between the two leading p T jets for several intervals of the leading jet p T (p max T ). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The measurements are done in the region \u03c0/2 < \u2206\u03c6 1,2 \u2264 \u03c0. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Measurement of inclusive 3-jet and 4-jet cross sections are also available in [8].",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 78,
                    "end": 81,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "[8]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Experimental and theoretical uncertainties are reduced by normalizing the \u2206\u03c6 1,2 distribution to the total dijet cross section. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The measurement is performed using data collected during 2016 with the CMS experiment at the CERN LHC, corresponding to an integrated luminosity of 35.9 f b \u22121 of proton-proton collisions at \u221a s = 13TeV . ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Concerning the final event selection, in this analysis first we consider all jets with a minimum p T of 100 GeV and |y| < 5. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Then for inclusive 2-jets events we require at least 2 jets whith |y 1 | < 2.5 and |y 2 | < 2.5. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "For inclusive 3-jet (4-jet) all jets must have |y| < 2.5.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Predictions from different MC event generators are compared to data. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The HERWIG++ and the PYTHIA8 event generators are considered. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 21,
                    "end": 27,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "PYTHIA",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Both of them are based on LO 2 \u2192 2 matrix element calculations. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "For PYTHIA8, the CUETP8M1 tune [9], which is based on NNPDF2.3LO [10,11], is considered, while HERWIG++ uses the CUETHppS1 tune [9], based on the CTEQ6L1 PDF set [12]. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 31,
                    "end": 34,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 65,
                    "end": 69,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[10,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 69,
                    "end": 72,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "11]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 128,
                    "end": 131,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 162,
                    "end": 166,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b11",
                    "text": "[12]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 10,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "PYTHIA",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The MADGRAPH [13] event generator provides LO matrix element calculations with up to four outgoing partons. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 13,
                    "end": 17,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b12",
                    "text": "[13]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The NNPDF2.3LO PDF set is used in the matrix element calculation. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "It is interfaced to PYTHIA8 with tune CUETP8M1. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 20,
                    "end": 26,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "PYTHIA",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "For the matching with PYTHIA8, the kt-MLM matching procedure [14] is used. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 61,
                    "end": 65,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b13",
                    "text": "[14]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 28,
                    "end": 29,
                    "type": "version",
                    "rawForm": "8",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "#software-simple-s4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Predictions based on NLO pQCD are considered using the POWHEG package [15,16,17] and the HERWIG7 [18] event generator. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 70,
                    "end": 74,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b14",
                    "text": "[15,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 74,
                    "end": 77,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b15",
                    "text": "16,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 77,
                    "end": 80,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b16",
                    "text": "17]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 97,
                    "end": 101,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b17",
                    "text": "[18]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The events simulated with POWHEG are matched to PYTHIA8 or to HERWIG++ parton showers and MPI, while HER-WIG7 uses similar parton shower and MPI models as HERWIG++. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 48,
                    "end": 54,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "PYTHIA",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In this analysis, POWHEG provides an NLO dijet calculation [19], referred to as POWHEG 2jet, and an NLO three-jet calculation [20], referred to as POWHEG 3jet, both using the NNPDF30nlo PDF set [21]. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 59,
                    "end": 63,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b18",
                    "text": "[19]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 126,
                    "end": 130,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b19",
                    "text": "[20]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 194,
                    "end": 198,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b20",
                    "text": "[21]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The POWHEG 2jet is matched to PYTHIA8 with tune CUETP8M1 and HERWIG++ with tune CUETHppS1, while the POWHEG 3jet is matched only to PYTHIA8 with tune CUETP8M1. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 30,
                    "end": 36,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "PYTHIA",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s6"
                },
                {
                    "start": 132,
                    "end": 138,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "PYTHIA",
                    "resp": "service",
                    "id": "software-simple-s7"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Predictions from the HERWIG7 event generator make use of NLO dijet matrix elements calculated with the MMHT 2014 PDF set [22] and use the default tune H7-UE-MMHT [18] for the UE simulation. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 121,
                    "end": 125,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b21",
                    "text": "[22]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 162,
                    "end": 166,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b17",
                    "text": "[18]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Parton shower contributions are matched to the matrix element within the MC@NLO procedure [23,24] through angular-ordered emissions.",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 90,
                    "end": 94,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b22",
                    "text": "[23,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 94,
                    "end": 97,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b23",
                    "text": "24]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The unfolded, normalized inclusive 2-jet cross sections differential in \u2206\u03c6 1,2 are shown in Fig. 1 for the various p max T regions considered. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 92,
                    "end": 98,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The distributions are strongly peaked at \u03c0 and become steeper with increasing p max T . ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Overlaid with the data are predictions from POWHEG 2jet + PYTHIA8 event generator. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The error bars on the data points represent the total experimental uncertainty, which is the quadratic sum of the statistical and systematic uncertainties.",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Figures 2 (left) shows the ratios of the PYTHIA8, HERWIG++, MADGRAPH + PYTHIA8 event generators predictions to the normalized inclusive 2-jet cross section differential in \u2206\u03c6 1,2 , for all p max T regions. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The solid band indicates the total experimental uncertainty and the error bars on the MC points represent their statistical uncertainties. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Among the LO dijet event generators HERWIG++ exhibits the largest deviations from the measurements. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "PYTHIA8 behaves much better than HERWIG++ exhibiting some deviations particular around \u2206\u03c6 = 5\u03c0/6. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The MAD-GRAPH + PYTHIA8 event generator provides the best description of the measurements.",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Figures 2 (right) shows the ratios of the POWHEG 2jet matched to PYTHIA8 and HERWIG++, POWHEG 3jet + PYTHIA8, and HERWIG7 event generators predictions to the normalized inclusive 2-jet cross section differential in \u2206\u03c6 1,2 , for all p max T regions. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The solid band indicates the total experimental uncertainty and the error bars on the MC points represent the statistical uncertainties in the simulated data. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The predictions of POWHEG 2jet or POWHEG 3jet exhibit large deviations from the measurements. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "It has been checked that POWHEG 2jet predictions at parton level, i.e. without the simulation of MPI, HAD and parton showers, give a reasonable description of the measurement for values of \u2206\u03c6 1,2 greater than \u2248 2\u03c0/3, while they completely fail for smaller values, where the parton shower has a crucial role. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Adding parton showers fills the phase space at low values of \u2206\u03c6 1,2 and brings the POWHEG 2jet predictions closer to data, however with the parameter setting used the agreement is not optimal. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Unfortunately, no big effect is observed when parton-shower is included. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Further investigation showed that the POWHEG 2jet calculation and the POWHEG three-jet calculation at LO are equivalent when initial-and final-state radiation is switched off.",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The predictions from POWHEG 2jet matched to PYTHIA8 are describing the normalized cross sections better than those where POWHEG 2jet is matched to HERWIG++. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Since the hard process calculation is the same, the difference between the two predictions is entirely due to different parton shower in PYTHIA8 and HERWIG++, which also use different \u03b1 S values for initialand final-state emissions, in addition to a different upper scale used for the parton shower simulation, which is higher in PYTHIA8 than in HERWIG++. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "The dijet NLO event generator HERWIG7 provides the best description of the measurements, showing a very large improvement in comparison to HERWIG++.",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "For this observable MC@NLO method of combining parton shower with the NLO parton level calculations has advantages compared to the POWHEG method.",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "All these observations emphasize the need to improve predictions for multijet production. ",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Similar observations, for the inclusive 2-jet cross sections differential in \u2206\u03c6 1,2 , were reported previously by CMS [5] at a different centre-of-mass energy.",
            "section": "Results and Conclusions.",
            "paragraph_rank": 10,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 118,
                    "end": 121,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ]
        },
